The paper presents a new end-to-end network for panoptic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach to cast the panoptic task into a dense pixel-wise classification task, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning models and neural networks, which are common in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed method, which involves metrics and performance analysis, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another possible category. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on image datasets, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
